The EU diplomacy chief Josep Borrell said provocations and incitements to hatred were continuing, and that deaths needed to be independently investigated. The electoral commission said Ouattara won 94% of the vote, which was boycotted by the opposition. Turnout was 54%. The opposition says it is creating a transitional government, describing Ouattara's third term run as an electoral coup. About 40 people were killed during campaigning and on election day. --BBC--